.TH SOPLOS-WEBAPP-MANAGER 1 "March 2026" "Soplos Linux" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
soplos-webapp-manager \- Create and manage isolated Web Applications (SSBs)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B soplos-webapp-manager
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B soplos-webapp-manager
is an elegant, lightweight Site Specific Browser (SSB) engine tailored for Soplos Linux. It effortlessly turns any website into a standalone, desktop-integrated application utilizing isolated browser profiles for maximum privacy and separation from your primary web session.
.PP
The application provides a graphical interface (GTK+ 3) to configure your webapps, download their icons dynamically (using DuckDuckGo's favicon API), and map them to standard standard Linux desktop entries.
.PP
By default, each WebApp is fully sandboxed in \fI~/.local/share/soplos-webapps/\fR avoiding cross-contamination with your personal web browsing.
.SH OPTIONS
.B soplos-webapp-manager
does not accept command-line options. It is a strictly graphical application.
